sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J34100
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: AND gate, 2x PoPS input, 1x PoPS output
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part will model a simple AND gate as it is known in the electrical engineering world. It produces only a high output if both input signals are also high.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: ETH Zurich 2006 iGEM team
